gomodel:SYNGO_1491  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Caldendrin and importin-alpha bind to jacob in a competitive manner (Fig. 5). Fig. 8: Caldendrin prevents shuttling of jacob to the nucleus.. Experimental description: \"Yeast two-hybrid screening was performed as described previously [63]. Library screening was done with a rat brain cDNA library in pACT2 (Matchmaker-GAL4 Two-Hybrid II; Clontech)\". \"Figure 5. Caldendrin and Importin-a Bind to Jacob in a Competitive Manner (A) Mapping the Caldendrin-Jacob interaction using the yeast two-hybrid assay\". Figure 5 legend\n\"Hippocampal primary cultures were prepared according to Goslin and Banker [7] using 19d rat embryos.\" Suppl. Information, Text S1\n\n17/11/2017 Pim\n- The over expressed caldendrin is of rat species. Personal communication with the authors: \"We cloned Caldendrin originally by screening a rat brain expression cDNA library with antibodies against the PSD protein fraction (PMID: 9694893). The YTH library used to screen for interaction partners including Jacob was also from rat.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" ;
        dc:date           "2018-01-25" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1491" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

